    "We discuss this effect in more detail in Section 4.3.",
    "Based on the cleaned samples, EzTaoX and JAVELIN yield comparable results for lag measurement accuracy.",
    "Figure 2 presents the difference between the recovered lag and the true simulated lag (∆lag) as a function of the true lag.",
    "The left column shows results from JAVELIN, while the right column displays results from EzTaoX.",
    "The top row corresponds to fits obtained using only the first 3 years of simulated LSST light curves, and the bottom row shows results based on the full 10-year simulated dataset."
